# ShivRide Admin Panel: Enterprise PRD & SOP Guide

This document provides an exhaustive overview of the **ShivRide Admin Panel**, covering its technical requirements, functional screens, and standard operating procedures for daily business operations.

---

## 1. Product Requirements Document (PRD)

### 1.1 Project Vision
To provide a robust, scalable, and real-time management interface for taxi and delivery business owners. The system is built on **Laravel 12** and **Vue 3 (Inertia.js)** for a seamless Single Page Application (SPA) experience.

### 1.2 Target Personas
1.  **Super Admin**: Full access to system configuration, payments, and master data.
2.  **Dispatcher**: Manages live ride requests and manual assignments.
3.  **Fleet Owner**: Manages their own set of drivers and vehicles.
4.  **Support Staff**: Handles tickets, SOS alerts, and customer queries.

---

### 1.3 Functional Modules (A-Z)

#### [A] Dashboard & Analytics
| Screen | Description | Key Metric |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Main Dashboard** | Overview of global operations. | Total Bookings, Active Drivers, Revenue. |
| **Owner Dashboard** | Fleet-specific statistics. | Fleet Revenue, Driver Performance. |
| **Real-time Charts** | Visual data trends. | Peak Hour Demand, Earnings vs. Payouts. |

#### [B] User Management
- **Passenger List**: Master record of all registered users. Includes personal details, wallet history, and ride logs.
- **Delete Requests**: Privacy compliance module to manage and approve account deletion requests.
- **Bulk Import**: Utility to import user data from external systems via CSV.

#### [C] Driver & Vehicle Operations
- **Driver Verification**: Multi-stage approval process for license, RC, and insurance documents.
- **Vehicle Types**: Configuration of categories (Budget, Luxury, Cargo, Outstation).
- **Driver Wallet**: Managing driver payouts, credit/debit adjustments, and negative balance thresholds.
- **Ratings & Reviews**: Feedback loops to maintain service quality.

#### [D] Geo-Spatial Management
- **Service Locations**: Onboarding new cities/regions into the network.
- **Zone Geometry**: Drawing polygonal boundaries for specific pricing or restrictions.
- **Heat Maps**: Dynamic visualization of high-demand areas.
- **God's Eye**: Live GPS tracking of all "Online" drivers on a single map interface.

#### [E] Pricing & Financials
- **Fare Configuration**: Base fare, distance charges, time charges, and waiting fees per zone.
- **Rental & Outstation**: Specialized pricing models for long-distance or hourly bookings.
- **Subscription Engine**: Tools for drivers to purchase plans instead of paying per-ride commissions.
- **Promotions**: Coupon code generation with complex logic (expiry, usage limits, user-specific).

#### [F] System Configuration
- **Third-Party Gateways**: API integration for Stripe, PayPal, Razorpay, Twilio, and Firebase.
- **Notifications**: Centralized push notification center for mass alerts.
- **CMS Builder**: Managing landing page content, FAQs, and legal documents (Privacy Policy).

---

## 2. Standard Operating Procedures (SOP)

### 2.1 Driver Onboarding SOP
> [!IMPORTANT]
> A driver cannot receive ride requests until their status is "Approved" and "Document Verified".

1.  **Step 1**: Monitor `Driver Management > Pending Drivers` for new registrations.
2.  **Step 2**: Open the Profile and click the **Documents** tab.
3.  **Step 3**: Verify validity dates on the License and Insurance.
4.  **Step 4**: Assign a **Vehicle Type** (Economy/Premium).
5.  **Step 5**: Toggle the status to **Approved**.

### 2.2 New Zone & Pricing Setup SOP
1.  **Creation**: Go to `Geo Fencing > Zone`. Use the drawing tool to mark the area.
2.  **Mapping**: Connect the Zone to a **Service Location** (City).
3.  **Pricing**: Navigate to `Price Management > Set Price`. Choose the Zone and Vehicle.
4.  **Surge Logic**: Add **Peak Zones** for specific times (e.g., peak office hours) if required.
5.  **Activation**: Ensure the "Active" toggle is ON.

### 2.3 Emergency (SOS) Management SOP
> [!CAUTION]
> SOS alerts should be addressed within 60 seconds of appearing on the dashboard.

1.  **Detection**: Click the blinking SOS icon on the top header.
2.  **Investigation**: View the live location and contact details of the Passenger and Driver.
3.  **Action**: Attempt to call both parties. If no response, escalate to local help authorities.
4.  **Tracking**: Use 'God's Eye' to see if any nearby drivers can assist.
5.  **Closure**: Document the incident and mark as "Resolved".

### 2.4 Payout & Withdrawal SOP
1.  **Report**: Pull the **Finance Report** at the end of the settlement cycle.
2.  **Verification**: Navigate to `Driver Wallet > Withdrawal Requests`.
3.  **Approval**: Verify the driver's current balance is > (Requested Amount + Charges).
4.  **Transfer**: Process the fund transfer via the integrated gateway.
5.  **Finalization**: Mark the status as "Paid" in the panel to update ledger entries.

---

## 3. Technical Reference

- **Frontend Core**: `resources/js/Pages/pages/overall-menu.vue` (Defines the sitemap).
- **Backend Logic**: `app/Http/Controllers/` (Each module has a dedicated controller).
- **Routes**: `routes/web/` folder contains modularized route definitions for each business area.
- **Mobile API**: `routes/api.php` handles the mobile app interactions.

---

> [!TIP]
> Use the **Audit Logs** (Others module) to track which admin made specific changes to pricing or driver status to ensure accountability.
